# Project constants

**What this file is:** The **only** place where project-wide parameter **names**, **values**, **formats**, and **constraints** are defined. Every other rule, doc, script, Terraform variable default, and generated artifact **references** these constant IDs — it does not re-declare values.

**When to use it:** Before writing or reviewing **any** rule (`.cursor/rules/**`), IaC (`infra/**`), Helm chart, port list, AWS name, tag map, CLI command default, or package identity field that needs a shared project parameter.

**How to use it:** Read **Rules** and **Constant groups** first; look up the constant ID in **Constants**; wire runtime values through `infra/aws/aws_tf/terraform.tfvars` and `local.solution` so they match this file; apply naming from **`.cursor/rules/infras/resource-naming.mdc`** and tagging from **`.cursor/rules/infras/resource-taging.mdc`** without duplicating values here.

---

## Rules (mandatory)

1. **Single source** — This file is the authoritative catalog; if a parameter appears here, nowhere else in `.cursor/rules/**` may state a literal value for it.
2. **Link, do not copy** — Other rules use `` `CONSTANT_ID` `` and link **`.cursor/rules/constants/constants.mdc`**; prose examples may show a value only by quoting the current row in **Constants**.
3. **No hard-coded parameters** — Forbidden in rules, modules, and docs: literal `ray-test`, `ray_test`, `017868795096`, `kt-acc`, `dev-0001-a1b2c3`, cost codes, emails, CIDRs, or tag defaults unless copied from **Constants** in the same change that updates this file.
4. **Owner sets values** — Project or solution owner updates **Constants** and matching `terraform.tfvars` / env files together; agents must not invent owners, URLs, versions, or account IDs.
5. **Derived constants** — Values built from other constants (e.g. `DEP_KEY`, `TAG_KEY_PROJECT_ID`) must use the formulas in **Constants**; never substitute ad hoc joins.
6. **Secrets excluded** — Access keys, session tokens, and passwords are **never** constants; only `AWS_CLI_PROFILE` name is stored — credentials live in `~/.aws/credentials` on the developer machine.
7. **Drift** — When live AWS or Terraform defaults disagree with **Constants**, treat as drift; reconcile IaC toward this file or update this file in the same PR as the IaC change.
8. **Physical AWS IDs** — Resource IDs (`vpc-…`, `subnet-…`, `sg-…`) are runtime-only; never add them to **Constants**.
9. **Naming and tagging** — Physical name patterns and tag application rules live in **`infras/resource-naming.mdc`** and **`infras/resource-taging.mdc`**; only **values** and **tag keys** live here.
10. **Group prefixes** — Every constant ID starts with its group prefix (`PRJ_`, `AWS_`, `DEP_`, `NET_`, `TAG_`); use the prefix to find the related group quickly.

---

## Constant groups

Constants are grouped by job. Each group has a **mandatory prefix** on every constant ID in that group.

| Order | Group | Prefix | Scope |
|-------|-------|--------|-------|
| 1 | **Project** | `PRJ_` | Product identity, display name, package id, solution metadata |
| 2 | **AWS account and CLI** | `AWS_` | Account id, CLI profile, region, output format |
| 3 | **Deployment** | `DEP_` | Environment, index, instance, composite deployment key |
| 4 | **Network** | `NET_` | VPC, subnets, security groups, EKS cluster name, AZ count |
| 5 | **Resource tagging** | `TAG_` | Mandatory L1 tag keys, values, and sentinels |

---

## Constants

One line per constant: **ID** — **Value** — **Use** — **Format / constraints**.

### Group 1 — Project (`PRJ_`)

1. **`PRJ_NAME`** — `Ray Test` — Human-readable product name in prose, headings, UI copy, and descriptions — Format: free text; no kebab/snake requirement.
2. **`PRJ_SLUG`** — `ray-test` — Kebab-case product slug for AWS physical names, scopes, `Application` tag, platform prefix, EKS cluster name — Format: lowercase `[a-z0-9-]`; single hyphens only; must not start or end with `-`; no `--`.
3. **`PRJ_PACKAGE`** — `ray_test` — Snake-case package id for Terraform `solution_name`, CloudWatch paths, Python/Node package `name` fields — Format: lowercase `[a-z0-9_]`; no `-`; maps to slug via `replace(_, "-")`.
4. **`PRJ_DESCRIPTION`** — `Ray Test primary AWS infrastructure.` — Tag `Description` and solution metadata — Format: free text; keep in sync with `solution_description` in tfvars.
5. **`PRJ_VERSION`** — `0.1.0` — Tag `Version` and release tracking — Format: semver `MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH`.
6. **`PRJ_RELEASE_DATE`** — `2026-05-16` — Tag `ReleaseDate` — Format: ISO date `YYYY-MM-DD`.

### Group 2 — AWS account and CLI (`AWS_`)

7. **`AWS_ACCOUNT_ID`** — `017868795096` — Allowed AWS account for all IaC and CLI in this repo — Format: exactly 12 digits; use in `allowed_account_ids` and Tier D name suffixes.
8. **`AWS_CLI_PROFILE`** — `kt-acc` — Local AWS CLI/SDK profile name (credentials not stored in repo) — Format: profile name string; sync from `infra/envs/dev/.env.aws` via `make/load-aws-creds.sh`.
9. **`AWS_DEFAULT_REGION`** — `us-east-1` — Default region for CLI, provider, and regional ARNs — Format: AWS region id `[a-z0-9-]+`.
10. **`AWS_OUTPUT_FORMAT`** — `json` — Default AWS CLI output format — Format: `json` | `text` | `table` | `yaml`.

### Group 3 — Deployment (`DEP_`)

Runtime source: **`infra/aws/aws_tf/terraform.tfvars`** (must match values below). Terraform exposes the same fields on **`local.solution`**.

11. **`DEP_ENVIRONMENT`** — `dev` — Logical environment for names, tags `Environment` / `DeploymentEnvironment`, and blast-radius — Format: one of `dev`, `qa`, `uat`, `prod`; lowercase; no `--`.
12. **`DEP_INDEX`** — `0001` — Four-digit deployment version index within the environment — Format: `[0-9]{4}`; range `0001`–`9999`; no `--`.
13. **`DEP_INSTANCE`** — `a1b2c3` — Six-character instance id for parallel stacks in one account — Format: `[a-z0-9]{6}`; lowercase; no `--`.
14. **`DEP_KEY`** — `dev-0001-a1b2c3` — Composite deployment id for Tier D names and tags — Format: `{DEP_ENVIRONMENT}-{DEP_INDEX}-{DEP_INSTANCE}`; single hyphens only; derived — never hard-code segments separately in names.

### Group 4 — Network (`NET_`)

Physical resource IDs are not constants. **`{prefix}`** = `PRJ_SLUG` (`ray-test`).

15. **`NET_VPC_CIDR`** — `10.0.0.0/16` — VPC address space for platform networking — Format: RFC1918 CIDR; `/16` required for current subnet carve plan.
16. **`NET_AZ_COUNT`** — `3` — Number of AZs for tiered subnets — Format: integer `1`–`3`; must match subnet rules below.
17. **`NET_VPC_NAME`** — `{prefix}-platform` — VPC `Name` tag and display — Example: `ray-test-platform` — Format: kebab; Tier P.
18. **`NET_EKS_CLUSTER_NAME`** — `{PRJ_SLUG}` — EKS cluster name and K8s namespace default — Value: `ray-test` — Format: equals `PRJ_SLUG`; Tier P.
19. **`NET_IGW_NAME`** — `{prefix}-igw` — Internet gateway `Name` tag — Example: `ray-test-igw` — Format: kebab; Tier P.
20. **`NET_SUBNET_ALB_PUBLIC`** — `{prefix}-alb-public-{n}` — Public ALB-only subnets; `{n}` = AZ index 1..3 — CIDR offsets `0`,`1`,`2` → `/24` per AZ — Format: public; dedicated to internet-facing ALBs.
21. **`NET_SUBNET_EKS_PRIVATE`** — `{prefix}-eks-private-{n}` — Private EKS, Fargate, nodes, interface VPC endpoints — CIDR offsets `10`,`11`,`12` — Format: private; `/24` per AZ.
22. **`NET_SUBNET_BASTION`** — `{prefix}-bastion-{n}` — Break-glass bastion subnets (SSM; no inbound SSH by default) — CIDR offsets `20`,`21`,`22` — Format: private; `/24` per AZ.
23. **`NET_SG_ALB`** — `{prefix}-alb` — Security group for internet-facing ALB — Example: `ray-test-alb`.
24. **`NET_SG_EKS_CLUSTER`** — `{prefix}-eks-cluster` — EKS control plane API security group — Example: `ray-test-eks-cluster`.
25. **`NET_SG_EKS_WORKLOADS`** — `{prefix}-eks-workloads` — Pod and node ENI security group — Example: `ray-test-eks-workloads`.
26. **`NET_SG_BASTION`** — `{prefix}-bastion` — Bastion security group — Example: `ray-test-bastion`.
27. **`NET_SG_VPC_ENDPOINTS`** — `{prefix}-vpc-endpoints` — Interface VPC endpoint security group — Example: `ray-test-vpc-endpoints`.
28. **`NET_SG_FSX_LUSTRE`** — `{prefix}-shared-lustre-sg` — FSx Lustre client security group — Example: `ray-test-shared-lustre-sg`.

**Subnet carve rule:** from `NET_VPC_CIDR`, use `cidrsubnet(vpc_cidr, 8, offset)` — one `/24` per AZ per tier; offsets in rows 20–22.

### Group 5 — Resource tagging (`TAG_`)

Application rules: **`.cursor/rules/infras/resource-taging.mdc`**. Wire L1 in **`infra/aws/aws_tf/providers.tf`** `default_tags`. Tag keys are PascalCase unless noted.

29. **`TAG_EMPTY`** — `""` — Sentinel for optional tags with no value (`ExpiresAt`, `ResourceGroup1`–`3`) — Format: empty string; do not omit L1 key unless AWS forbids empty on that resource type.
30. **`TAG_KEY_APPLICATION`** — AWS key `Application` — Value: `PRJ_SLUG` (`ray-test`) — Product/application dimension for cost and inventory.
31. **`TAG_KEY_PROJECT`** — AWS key `Project` — Value: `PRJ_PACKAGE` (`ray_test`) — Snake-case project name tag.
32. **`TAG_KEY_PROJECT_ID`** — AWS key `ProjectId` — Value: `{PRJ_SLUG}-{DEP_KEY}` — Example: `ray-test-dev-0001-a1b2c3` — Stack grouping id; derived.
33. **`TAG_KEY_DESCRIPTION`** — AWS key `Description` — Value: `PRJ_DESCRIPTION` — Free text; max practical AWS tag length 256 chars.
34. **`TAG_KEY_VERSION`** — AWS key `Version` — Value: `PRJ_VERSION` — Semver string.
35. **`TAG_KEY_RELEASE_DATE`** — AWS key `ReleaseDate` — Value: `PRJ_RELEASE_DATE` — ISO date.
36. **`TAG_KEY_MANAGED_BY`** — AWS key `ManagedBy` — Value: `Terraform` — Literal; do not change without migration plan.
37. **`TAG_KEY_DEPLOYMENT_ENVIRONMENT`** — AWS key `DeploymentEnvironment` — Value: `DEP_ENVIRONMENT` — Same allowed values as row 11.
38. **`TAG_KEY_ENVIRONMENT`** — AWS key `Environment` — Value: `DEP_ENVIRONMENT` — Allowed: `dev`, `qa`, `uat`, `prod`.
39. **`TAG_KEY_DEPLOYMENT_INDEX`** — AWS key `DeploymentIndex` — Value: `DEP_INDEX` — Four digits.
40. **`TAG_KEY_DEPLOYMENT_INSTANCE`** — AWS key `DeploymentInstance` — Value: `DEP_INSTANCE` — Six `[a-z0-9]`.
41. **`TAG_KEY_DEPLOYMENT_KEY`** — AWS key `DeploymentKey` — Value: `DEP_KEY` — Derived composite.
42. **`TAG_KEY_DEPLOYED_AT`** — AWS key `DeployedAt` — Value: `2026-06-11T12:00:00Z` — UTC ISO-8601 deploy timestamp — Format: `YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SSZ`; tfvars `deployed_at`.
43. **`TAG_KEY_DEPLOYED_BY`** — AWS key `DeployedBy` — Value: `platform@example.com` — Deployer email — Format: RFC5322-like email; tfvars `deployed_by`.
44. **`TAG_KEY_EXPIRES_AT`** — AWS key `ExpiresAt` — Value: `2026-12-11T12:00:00Z` or `TAG_EMPTY` — Scheduled teardown hint — Format: UTC ISO-8601 or `""`; tfvars `expires_at`.
45. **`TAG_KEY_RESOURCE_OWNER`** — AWS key `ResourceOwner` — Value: `platform@example.com` — Accountable owner — Format: email or team id string; tfvars `resource_owner`.
46. **`TAG_KEY_OWNER_EMAIL`** — AWS key `OwnerEmail` — Value: `platform@example.com` — Owner contact — Format: email; tfvars `owner_email`.
47. **`TAG_KEY_CREATED_BY`** — AWS key `CreatedBy` — Value: `platform@example.com` — Creator email — Format: email; tfvars `created_by`.
48. **`TAG_KEY_AUTOMATION_IGNORE`** — AWS key `AutomationIgnore` — Value: `false` — When `true`, all repo automation must skip the resource — Format: string `"true"` | `"false"`; tfvars `automation_ignore` bool.
49. **`TAG_VALUE_AUTOMATION_IGNORE_TRUE`** — `true` — Literal tag value for ignore-on — String `"true"` on AWS tag.
50. **`TAG_VALUE_AUTOMATION_IGNORE_FALSE`** — `false` — Default automation tag value — String `"false"` on AWS tag.
51. **`TAG_KEY_RESOURCE_GROUP_1`** — AWS key `ResourceGroup1` — Value: `TAG_EMPTY` — Optional grouping dimension 1 — Format: free text or empty; tfvars `resource_group_1`.
52. **`TAG_KEY_RESOURCE_GROUP_2`** — AWS key `ResourceGroup2` — Value: `TAG_EMPTY` — Optional grouping dimension 2 — tfvars `resource_group_2`.
53. **`TAG_KEY_RESOURCE_GROUP_3`** — AWS key `ResourceGroup3` — Value: `TAG_EMPTY` — Optional grouping dimension 3 — tfvars `resource_group_3`.
54. **`TAG_KEY_COST_CODE`** — AWS key `CostCode` — Value: `CC-ARB-001` — Finance chargeback code — Format: org-defined code string; tfvars `cost_code`.
55. **`TAG_KEY_COST_CENTER`** — AWS key `CostCenter` — Value: `CC-ARB-001` — Cost Explorer allocation — Format: use tfvars `cost_center` when set, else `cost_code`.
56. **`TAG_KEY_DEPARTMENT`** — AWS key `Department` — Value: `Engineering` — Owning department — Format: free text; tfvars `department`.
57. **`TAG_KEY_ACCOUNT_ID`** — AWS key `AccountId` — Value: `AWS_ACCOUNT_ID` — AWS account dimension on resources — Format: 12-digit string.

**L2 Well-Architected tag keys** (values set per module — not duplicated here): `Owner`, `Service`, `Component`, `DataClassification`, `Backup`, `Criticality` — see **`resource-taging.mdc`**.

